<p>I am using Apache Camel in  OSGI scenario using Karaf in version 2.15.1. I am using the exchange.getExchangeId() to print the exchange id in a request/reply. The exchange pattern is set to InOnly. The route looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;route id="ip_client_rpc"&gt;     &lt;from uri="restlet:http://localhost:7070/lsp/patron/id?restletMethod=POST&amp;amp;synchronous=true"/&gt;      &lt;to uri="log:${headers}"/&gt;     &lt;setExchangePattern pattern="InOnly"/&gt;     &lt;process ref="rabbit_client"/&gt;     &lt;to uri="log:${headers}"/&gt;   &lt;/route&gt; </code></pre>  <p>However when I print the exchange id sent to the rabbitmq queue it always ends with an even number.</p>  <pre><code>Request from client:ID-VirtualDev-49301-1443430754519-5-6 Request from client:ID-VirtualDev-49301-1443430754519-5-8 Request from client:ID-VirtualDev-49301-1443430754519-5-10 Request from client:ID-VirtualDev-49301-1443430754519-5-12 Request from client:ID-VirtualDev-49301-1443430754519-5-14 </code></pre>  <p>Is there a reason why the final digit is always even? Is there another exchange being created that I am missing?</p>  <p>Thanks</p>